From b270b4ef4d22bde06bb5e87a02fea0a083e7aa85 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ESTI Contributors <esti@example.local>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 07:14:15 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] Dashboard UX pass: priority ladder, single type scale,
 equal-height rows

Addresses dashboard feedback (too much information, scattered text, uneven
cards, blank space):

- Strict priority order top-to-bottom: KPI strip -> Action Center ->
  Financial health -> Project health -> Client signals -> Team performance ->
  Quality intelligence -> Statutory & activity -> admin toggles
- KPI strip reduced from six chips (4+2 ragged rows) to four balanced chips,
  one per question: Ready to bill, Outstanding (overdue folded into its tag),
  Active projects (risk folded into its tag), Team utilization; revision risk
  moved into the Quality intelligence zone
- One typography scale everywhere: h1 page title, h3 zone headers via a single
  SectionHeader component, h4 tile titles, h2 reserved for KPI values; removed
  pictograms and category-tag tile headers that scattered the visual line
- Equal-height rows: every tile uses esti-fill, both financial charts share one
  240px height, Revision/Technical tiles use matching five-row label/value lists
- Less data per tile: action lists capped at 4, project table at 8 rows, client
  table at 6, team cards at 4 (one exact row), activity feed at 4 events
- Statutory filing tiles compacted to label + due tag (dates dropped)
- Action Center count tag no longer stretches; team cards are clickable
  through to /performance

Co-Authored-By: Codex Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
